Sentencas: Samples of lanthanum-strontium cuprate LaSrCuO3.61 are synthesized by a solid-phase method at 1473 K, in air.
Titulo: Lanthanum-strontium cuprate: A promising cathodic material for solid oxide fuel cells

Sentencas: Electron diffraction patterns reveal low-intensity satellites whose position is described in the reciprocal space by the (3 + 2)-dimensional space group I4/mmm(alpha alpha 0, alpha-alpha 0)00mg.
Titulo: Lanthanum-strontium cuprate: A promising cathodic material for solid oxide fuel cells

Sentencas: Using a five-layer cell LaSrCuO4-delta vertical bar YSZ vertical bar LaSrCuO4-delta vertical bar YSZ vertical bar LaSrCuO4-delta prepared by isostatic hot pressing, the ionic component of conductivity of LaSrCuO4-delta is determined (sigma(1179K) = 3.8 x 10(-3) S cm(-1)), which is commensurate with other mixed conductors based on complex oxides of cobalt and iron.
Titulo: Lanthanum-strontium cuprate: A promising cathodic material for solid oxide fuel cells
